The paper proposes a feature selection algorithm for machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of Centred Kernel Target Alignment (KTA) suggests a focus on machine learning and pattern recognition, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions bioinformatics, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of probabilistic guarantees suggests a focus on theoretical computer science, which is covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
